Wow I found a new collard recipe. I have cooked collards/turnip greens for years but always with a few turnips and boiled them first then added the greens only until they wilted since I like my veggies crispy. This time I looked for something different and found it in this recipe. I pity the people with their over cooked mushy collards and I've had them. I used the instructions for this receipe but I bought a pound of bacon bits and trimmed the fat off and rendered it then discarded the fat and sauteed the meat until done. I also love turnips so I used one large turnip and sliced it thin into small slices and cooked it until just done with the bacon. If you have people in your family who turn up their nose at the word TURNIP, they will think they are eating potatoes,(mine do). After the bacon and turnips are done to my liking I added a little white wine, stir fried the sliced collards mixed with turnip greens until just wilted. I also added some pepper flakes along with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Very good and healthy.

