Rating: 0
Modified as follows: 4 strips thick bacon, diced. 1 red pepper, 1/4" x 2" strips. 2/3# collard greens, rolled and cut 3/16" as per original instructions. Fried bacon in sauteuse over high heat. Removed bacon and most of oil. Added red pepper strips and sauteed until softened. Removed. Added cut collard greens. Sauteed 2 - 2 1/2 minutes. Added back bacon and red pepper strips. Added generous grind black pepper and a whiff of balsamic vinegar. Tossed. Served as accompaniment to original recipe black bean/Columbian chorizo sausage soup. Wine was inexpensive Spanish Tempranillo. Modestly acknowledged the applause.

