Rating: 4
For some reason unbeknownst to me, I decided to plant some collard greens in our deck garden a few months ago. They quickly thrived and started to crowd some of the other plants in the large planter box. When I read this recipe it seemed timely to harvest some of the greens and try this Brazilian dish. I now know that it was truly fate that had me plant the collard greens as this is another recipe that is so simple and so good. The recipe is awesome. I will always maintain a few collard greens in the garden so we can make this again and again. I noticed a mistake in the recipe online compared to the magazine. The collard greens should be sliced no thicker than 1/8 inch not the 3/4 as shown online. I also used leaves that were about 6 inches across which is probably a little smaller than what is commonly found in the produce market.